{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":32107,"record_hash":"sha256:a6b58c820ef323a560007559a118864317689fbcb5ffe002c7a7a9163378a935","timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:54:25.388Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n- [scoped_sync.rs]([REDACTED:entropy].rs:35): If the remote exists but `refs/meta/agentlog` is missing, a stale local tracking ref can make sync incorrectly return `up_to_date` instead of recreating the remote ref. `fetch_scope_ref()` returns `false`, but the old `refs/meta/remotes/agentlog` is still compared against the local ref at lines 56-64. This violates the lifecycle note’s “missing remote ref should create it on push” behavior after a previous sync or deleted remote ref. Ignore/delete tracking state when the remote ref is absent, or only use the tracking equality shortcut after a successful fetch.\\n\\n- [Cargo.toml](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/Cargo.toml:15): GitButler now depends on `git-meta-lib` via `path = \\\"../../../git-meta/...\\\"`, and [Cargo.lock](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/Cargo.lock:3907) dropped the git source. That is fine for local integration testing, but it is not landable unless everyone/build CI has the sibling checkout. Before merging GitButler, this needs to point back to a published/git revision or be handled as an intentional workspace setup.\\n\\n- [schema.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/db/schema.rs:91): `sync_scope_state` looks like premature bookkeeping. The scoped serializer reads it and discards it ([serialize.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/serialize.rs:566)), always does a full rebuild, and then advances `last_materialized` during serialization ([serialize.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/serialize.rs:685)), which makes the name misleading. For this POC, I’d either remove the table/migration/store methods entirely or wire the marker into a real scoped incremental/needs-materialize invariant. As-is it is bloat and an attractive future footgun.\\n\\n**Validation**\\nRan:\\n- `cargo test -p git-meta-lib --test exchange scoped`\\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog sync`\\n\\nBoth passed. The tests emitted existing `git-meta-lib` dead-code warnings in prune/serialize.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:54:25.388Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}